Reasoning: The paper analyzes a dataset of YouTube video transcripts and examines sentiment surrounding keywords before and after the Unite the Right rally. This suggests a focus on natural language processing and sentiment analysis, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper explores potential effects of the rally on social movements, which could be categorized under social networks (cs.SI) or social dynamics (cs.SD). The study also touches on political sentiment and discourse, which could fall under cyberpolitics (cs.CY) or social and information networks (cs.SOC).
